1
00:00:06,740 --> 00:00:07,460
WHO ARE YOU?

2
00:00:08,120 --> 00:00:10,330
YOU WERE MY FIRST KISS.

3
00:00:10,580 --> 00:00:11,920
YOU WERE MY FIRST KISS,TOO.

4
00:00:12,340 --> 00:00:14,460
YOU TOUCH MURDER VICTIMS, YOU ASK WHO KILLED THEM.

5
00:00:14,580 --> 00:00:16,400
YOU TOUCH THEM AGAIN, THEY GO BACK TO BEING DEAD,

6
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:17,640
AND YOU COLLECT THE REWARD?

7
00:00:17,790 --> 00:00:18,930
THAT'S IT IN A NUTSHELL.

8
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:20,780
- ARE YOU THE BUSINESS PARTNER?
- YES,MA'AM.

9
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:22,510
DOESN'T SHE LOOK A LOT LIKE THAT DEAD GIRL?

10
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:25,060
SHE LOOKS EXACTLY LIKE THAT DEAD GIRL.

11
00:00:25,330 --> 00:00:27,700
DO YOU...TOUCH ANYTHING?

12
00:00:27,850 --> 00:00:29,340
I T-TOUCH LOTS OF THINGS.

13
00:00:30,070 --> 00:00:31,070
DOES HE TOUCH YOU?

14
00:00:31,590 --> 00:00:33,220
I'D KISS YOU IF IT WOULDN'T KILL ME.

15
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:35,930
Emerson: ARE YOU IN LOVE WITH HER? IT'S THAT LEVEL OF STUPID.

16
00:00:36,080 --> 00:00:37,930
I KIND OF KILLED HER DAD WHEN I WAS 10.

17
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:39,000
SHE DOESN'T KNOW.

18
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:42,170
I JUST THOUGHT MY WORLD WOULD BE A BETTER PLACE IF YOU WERE IN IT.

19
00:00:42,170 --> 00:00:43,500
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE I SHOULD KNOW?

20
00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:45,350
NO.

21
00:00:54,740 --> 00:00:57,460
Narrator: AT THIS VERY MOMENT, IN THE TOWN OF NORTH THRUSH,

22
00:00:57,590 --> 00:01:03,190
YOUNG NED WAS 9 YEARS,33 WEEKS,6 DAYS,20 HOURS, AND 34 MINUTES OLD.

23
00:01:03,580 --> 00:01:05,830
HE STOOD ON THE EXACT SPOT WHERE,

24
00:01:05,950 --> 00:01:07,830
4 WEEKS AND 2 DAYS PREVIOUSLY,

25
00:01:07,990 --> 00:01:11,810
HIS FATHER HAD DEPOSITED HIM AT THE LONGBURROW SCHOOL FOR BOYS.

26
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:18,950
AS YOUNG NED'S MOTHER HAD DIED RECENTLY,

27
00:01:19,260 --> 00:01:22,810
THERE WAS REASSURING PHYSICAL CONTACT AND PARTING WORDS.

28
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:24,510
"I'LL BE BACK."

29
00:01:25,260 --> 00:01:26,470
HE LIED.

30
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:30,380
THE SADNESS AND DREAD WHICH THE BOY FELT

31
00:01:30,510 --> 00:01:32,900
WERE NOT SO MUCH A PRODUCT OF THE LONGBURROW SCHOOL.

32
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:36,660
YOUNG NED'S ACUTE DISCOMFORT CAME FROM THE KNOWLEDGE

33
00:01:36,780 --> 00:01:40,210
THAT WHEN HE TOUCHED A DEAD THING,IT CAME BACK TO LIFE.

34
00:01:40,450 --> 00:01:42,510
THE OTHER BOYS ASSUMED HIS INTROVERTED NATURE

35
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:44,970
WAS A PRODUCT OF WEAKNESS AND CODDLING.

36
00:01:45,340 --> 00:01:48,000
THINKING OF REVENGE AND ALSO NOT THINKING AT ALL,

37
00:01:48,250 --> 00:01:51,890
YOUNG NED VOLUNTEERED TO ASSIST WITH THAT DAY'S SCIENCE PROJECT.

38
00:01:54,910 --> 00:01:58,590
YOUNG NED'S SECRET GIFT WAS GOVERNED BY TEE SIMPLE RULES --

39
00:01:58,950 --> 00:02:01,770
TOUCH A DEAD THING ONCE,ALIVE.

40
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,730
TOUCH A DEAD THING AGAIN...

41
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:27,240
...DEAD FOREVER.

42
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:38,990
KEEP A DEAD THING ALIVE FOR MORE THAN A MINUTE...

43
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:42,390
AND SOMETHING ELSE HAS TO DIE.

44
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:47,610
HIS GIFT HAD,ONCE AGAIN, BROUGHT HIM GREAT DISTRESS IN PLACE OF GREAT JOY.

45
00:02:47,910 --> 00:02:52,710
HE VOWED TO KEEP THE STRANGE DETAILS OF HIS STRANGE LIFE SECRET FROM THE WORLD FOREVER.

46
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:54,980
ARE YOU RESPONSIBLE FOR THIS?

47
00:02:56,800 --> 00:03:01,190
Narrator: SO,YOUNG NED DID WHAT HIS FATHER HAD DONE TO HIM ONLY 31 DAYS BEFORE.

48
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:02,070
NO.

49
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:03,440
Narrator: HE LIED.

50
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:07,860
FOR THE NEXT 19 YEARS, 29 WEEKS,AND 2 DAYS,

51
00:03:07,990 --> 00:03:10,350
KEEPING SECRETS WORKED BEAUTIFULLY.

52
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:20,170
THE BOY BECAME THE PIE MAKER,

53
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:23,010
AND THE PIE MAKER DECEIVED WITH EASE...

54
00:03:23,380 --> 00:03:25,860
- UNTIL CHUCK.- THIS IS STRANGE.

55
00:03:26,290 --> 00:03:28,120
Narrator: CHARLOTTE CHARLES HAD BEEN ALIVE

56
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:34,200
FOR 28 YEARS,24 WEEKS,3 DAYS, 11 HOURS,AND 51 MINUTES BEFORE SHE WAS MURDERED.

57
00:03:35,010 --> 00:03:36,070
IS THIS STRANGE?

58
00:03:36,230 --> 00:03:37,640
THIS IS NOT STRANGE.UNUSUAL,

59
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:40,570
MAYBE ECCENTRIC, IN A QUAINT WAY, LIKE DESSERT SPOONS.

60
00:03:40,670 --> 00:03:42,300
Narrator: REVIVED BY THE PIE MAKER

61
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,910
AND GIVEN A SECOND CHANCE AT LIFE,

62
00:03:44,340 --> 00:03:45,770
SHE HAD MANY QUESTIONS.

63
00:03:45,890 --> 00:03:48,190
I HAVE SO MANY QUESTIONS, MY MIND WANDERS.

64
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,820
YOU NEED TO FEED IT WARM MILK AND A TURKEY SANDWICH.

65
00:03:50,950 --> 00:03:53,130
LET IT CURL UP IN A SUNNY SPOT AND TAKE A NAP.

66
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,790
I MISS MY AUNTS.

67
00:03:55,130 --> 00:03:58,040
OF COURSE. DO YOU MISS THEM A LOT?

68
00:03:59,490 --> 00:04:00,330
A LITTLE.

69
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:04,580
ALL THE TIME?

70
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:07,400
NOW AND THEN.

71
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:11,410
Narrator: AS CHUCK SPOKE,SHE REALIZED HER SECRETS WERE "REALLY A LOT"

72
00:04:11,570 --> 00:04:14,600
AND "EVERY MINUTE," IN THAT ORDER.

73
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:17,170
HOW MANY PEOPLE HAVE YOU TOUCHED?

74
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,680
PEOPLE OR ANIMALS? CROSSING.

75
00:04:18,870 --> 00:04:21,590
DIGBY DOESN'T COUNT. DIGBY DOES COUNT.

76
00:04:21,710 --> 00:04:23,410
NO ONE'S BEEN THROUGH AS MUCH WITH ME AS DIGBY.

77
00:04:23,540 --> 00:04:25,410
HOW MANY PEOPLE HAVE YOU BROUGHT BACK TO LIFE?

78
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:28,690
IT'S NOT LIKE I WALK AROUND REVIVING CHILDHOOD SWEETHEARTS WILLY-NILLY.

79
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:31,420
WELL,WHAT ABOUT EMERSON,HUH? OH,COMING THROUGH!

80
00:04:31,790 --> 00:04:33,450
YOU TOUCHED LOTS OF PEOPLE WITH EMERSON.

81
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:34,190
FOR WORK.

82
00:04:34,310 --> 00:04:35,880
JUST BECAUSE YOU KILL THEM AGAIN AS SOON AS YOU GET WHAT YOU WANT

83
00:04:36,010 --> 00:04:37,770
DOESN'T MAKE IT ANY DIFFERENT. YES,IT DOES.

84
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,530
COMING THROUGH.

85
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,180
AND CAN WE NOT SAY "KILL"? I TOUCH THEM AGAIN IS ALL,

86
00:04:49,310 --> 00:04:50,910
AND THEY SNAP RIGHT BACK TO THE WAY THEY'RE SUPPOSED TO BE.

87
00:04:51,070 --> 00:04:52,190
AM I THE RUBBER BAND THAT BROKE?

88
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,790
CHUCK,YOU'RE THE ONLY HUMAN BEING

89
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:55,820
I'VE EVER MADE ALIVE AGAIN TO STAY.

90
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,040
Narrator: HE LIED.

91
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:02,520
IN FACT,THE PIE MAKER HAD KEPT ONE OTHER PERSON ALIVE

92
00:05:02,650 --> 00:05:04,040
FOR LONGER THAN A MINUTE.

93
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:06,930
USING THE GIFT TO TEMPORARILY REVIVE HIS OWN MOTHER,

94
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:12,090
THE UNINTENDED EFFECT ON CHUCK'S FATHER HAD BEEN MORE PERMANENT.

95
00:05:14,150 --> 00:05:19,030
THPIE MAKER OFTEN ASKED HIMSELF IF HE WOULD EVER BE ABLE TO TELL CHUCK THIS SECRET.

96
00:05:19,030 --> 00:05:20,090
YOUR EYE'S TWITCHING.

97
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,000
IS IT?

98
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,360
THIS IS SUCH A SMALL CHEESE BOX.

99
00:05:28,260 --> 00:05:30,900
Narrator: THE AUNTS WHO HAD RAISED CHUCK HAD TAUGHT HER TO BELIEVE

100
00:05:31,050 --> 00:05:33,260
THAT THE LARGE WHITE APPLIANCE IN THE KITCHEN

101
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:35,420
HAD A FAIRLY NARROW PURPOSE.

102
00:05:35,550 --> 00:05:37,640
AUNT LILY,IS IT OKAY TO FREEZE THE CAMEMBERT?

103
00:05:37,770 --> 00:05:39,830
I'D RATHER NOT WEDGE IT BETWEEN THE EDAM AND THE PANEER!

104
00:05:39,990 --> 00:05:41,380
OR I COULD AIR OUT THE GOUDA!

105
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:44,570
Narrator: IN FACT,YOUNG CHUCK DID NOT REFER TO A REFRIGERATOR

106
00:05:44,690 --> 00:05:47,960
AS ANYTHING BUT A CHEESE B UNTIL SHE WAS 17.

107
00:05:50,830 --> 00:05:53,710
AS CHUCK CONSIDERED THE LIFE SHE COULD NEVER GO BACK TO,

108
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:58,320
OLIVE SNOOK CONSIDERED THE CHANGES IN HER OWN LIFE --

109
00:05:58,480 --> 00:06:01,420
FOREMOST,THE MYSTERIOUS BRUNETTE ENCROACHING

110
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:03,540
ON THE MAN SHE HERSELF LOVED.

111
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:06,870
FROM HER PERCH,THE JEALOUS YET AGILE NEIGHBOR

112
00:06:06,990 --> 00:06:10,270
WAS ABLE TO CONFIRM ONLY ONE PLEASING DETAIL.

113
00:06:10,390 --> 00:06:12,470
THERE'S A SURPRISING LACK OF PHYSICAL CONTACT.

114
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,290
OH,CRAP.

115
00:06:16,050 --> 00:06:17,530
Narrator: ONE MILE TO THE WEST,

116
00:06:17,660 --> 00:06:19,750
EMERSON COD WAS ALSO NOT THRILLED.

117
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:23,240
DURING TIMES OF STRESS OR ANXIETY,HE LIKED TO KNIT.

118
00:06:23,610 --> 00:06:26,240
SINCE THE ARRIVAL OF THE DEAD GIRL WHO WAS NOT DEAD,

119
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:29,660
HE FOUND THE STOCKINETTE STITCH TO BE ESPECIALLY RELAXING.

120
00:06:30,210 --> 00:06:31,360
EMERSON COD.

121
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:35,030
Narrator: BUT NO STITCH WAS A SUBSTITUTE FOR A GOOD MURDER CASE.

122
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:36,100
THANKS. GOT IT.

123
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:43,850
MEET ME AT THE MORGUE IN 15 MINUTES.

124
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:48,390
Narrator: AS HE FINISHED PEARLING THE ROW, HE WISHED ALOUD...

125
00:06:48,630 --> 00:06:49,820
SHE BETTER NOT COME.

126
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:56,310
HI,EMERSON.

127
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,520
ISN'T THIS EXCITING?

128
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:06,690
HEY!

129
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:08,910
WHAT'S SHE DOING HERE?

130
00:07:09,060 --> 00:07:10,140
SAID SHE DIDN'T CLIMB OUT OF A COFFIN

131
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:11,240
FOR ME TO KEEP HER IN A BOX.

132
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,310
SHE THE BOSS OF YOU?

133
00:07:12,550 --> 00:07:13,400
I'M THE BOSS OF ME.

134
00:07:13,530 --> 00:07:14,440
DEAD GIRL'S GOT TO GO.

135
00:07:14,630 --> 00:07:15,680
DEAD GIRL'S NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

136
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:16,650
YOU DON'T KNOW NOTHING ABOUT HER

137
00:07:16,810 --> 00:07:18,200
EXCEPT SHE HAD SOFT LIPS WHEN SHE WAS 10.

138
00:07:18,390 --> 00:07:19,300
THAT SHOULD BE ENOUGH.

139
00:07:19,450 --> 00:07:20,270
WELL,I DON'T LIKE IT.

140
00:07:28,810 --> 00:07:29,690
[ KNOCKING ] HEY!

141
00:07:33,150 --> 00:07:34,180
WHAT DID YOU GUYS TALK ABOUT?

142
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:35,610
I'D REALLY LIKE TO GET OUT OF THIS CAR SOON.

143
00:07:35,730 --> 00:07:37,760
IS HE UPSET YOU BROUGHT YOUR CHILDHOOD SWEETHEART BACK TO LIFE?

144
00:07:37,890 --> 00:07:38,830
HE BARELY KNOWS YOU'RE HERE.

145
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:45,250
Narrator: IN FACT,EMERSON COD HAD FINISHED KNITTING A SWEATER VEST

146
00:07:45,370 --> 00:07:48,510
AND TWO HANDGUN COZIES IN THE WEEK SINCE CHUCK'S RETURN.

147
00:07:49,420 --> 00:07:50,420
SWEET.

148
00:07:51,580 --> 00:07:53,400
DO I REALLY HAVE TO SIT IN BACK FROM NOW ON?

149
00:07:53,550 --> 00:07:54,680
IT'S FOR YOUR OWN SAFETY.

150
00:07:54,830 --> 00:07:55,800
YOU SOUND LIKE MY DAD.

151
00:07:55,930 --> 00:07:57,900
IF MY HAND BRUSHES YOURS, YOU'D BE DEAD.

152
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:00,010
HE DIDN'T SAY THAT.

153
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:07,020
SO IT'S PROBABLY BETTER IF YOU STAY IN THE CAR FOR THESE MORGUE VISITS.

154
00:08:07,150 --> 00:08:08,640
SOMEONE MIGHT RECOGNIZE YOU.

155
00:08:09,210 --> 00:08:10,520
YOU REALLY CAN'T COME IN.

156
00:08:11,460 --> 00:08:13,930
DID I SAY "CAN"?BECAUSE I SWALLOW MY CONSONANTS SOMETIMES.

157
00:08:14,210 --> 00:08:17,300
"N'T. N'T."CAN'T COME IN.

158
00:08:17,850 --> 00:08:18,850
[ CLEARS THROAT ] GOT THAT HIT-AND-RUN?

159
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,460
WE'RE FROM THE GOVERNMENT SAFETY PLACE?

160
00:08:21,570 --> 00:08:22,730
[ With teeth clenched ] IS THAT A QUESTION?

161
00:08:22,850 --> 00:08:23,970
GOVERNMENT SAFETY PLACE.

162
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,100
Narrator: THE FACTS WERE THESE.

163
00:08:29,220 --> 00:08:30,530
ONE BERNARD SLAYBECK,

164
00:08:30,650 --> 00:08:32,960
AN UNMARRIED AUTOMOTIVE SAFETY SPECIALIST --

165
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:36,320
35 YEARS,10 WEEKS,7 HOURS, AND 3 MINUTES OLD --

166
00:08:36,570 --> 00:08:38,570
WAS FOUND DEAD BY THE SIDE OF THE ROAD...

167
00:08:44,990 --> 00:08:47,720
...THE APPARENT VICTIM OF A HIT-AND-RUN DRIVER.

168
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:52,000
Narrator: AS THERE WERE NO WITNESSES, THE POLICE ARE OFFERING A REWARD

169
00:08:52,130 --> 00:08:55,010
FOR INFORMATION LEADING TO THE ARREST OF THE KILLER.

170
00:08:55,130 --> 00:08:56,110
I'M GONNA WAIT BACK HERE.

171
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:57,710
YOU DON'T LIKE DEAD BODIES, DO YOU?

172
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:59,200
NOT WHEN THEY SIT UP AND TALK.

173
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,120
POOR MAN. JUSTOUCH IT.

174
00:09:01,410 --> 00:09:02,480
I'M STARTING THE WATCH.

175
00:09:05,470 --> 00:09:06,020
HEY. HEY.

176
00:09:07,230 --> 00:09:08,350
WHY IS EVERYTHING SO BLURRY?

177
00:09:08,470 --> 00:09:11,080
PROBABLY BECAUSE YOUR EYEBALLS ARE FLAT. ASK THE QUESTION.

178
00:09:11,170 --> 00:09:13,450
MR. SLAYBECK,DO YOU -- DO YOU HAVE ANY LAST REQUESTS,

179
00:09:13,450 --> 00:09:15,420
UNFINISHED BUSINESS FROM THIS LIFE WE CAN HELP YOU WITH?

180
00:09:15,580 --> 00:09:17,060
DON'T LET HER DO THIS. IS THIS HEAVEN?

181
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,310
COULD BE. NO,IT'S NOT.

182
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:21,070
IS THAT GOD? NO,IT'S NOT.

183
00:09:21,230 --> 00:09:22,560
I'M CONFUSED, BECAUSE I'M A BUDDHIST.

184
00:09:22,690 --> 00:09:24,240
BUDDHISM IS FASCINATING, ISN'T IT?

185
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:25,820
DID IT HELP YOU IN YOUR FINAL MOMENTS?

186
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,240
SHE'S WASTING MY MINUTE.

187
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,550
WHAT'S WITH THIS MINUTE? AND WHEN DID IT BECOME YOUR MINUTE?

188
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:30,660
SURE THE HELL AIN'T YOURS.

189
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:33,370
HEY,IT'S EVERYONE'S MINUTE, OR,UH,22 SECONDS.

190
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:34,670
CAN YOU GET A MESSAGE TO EARTH?

191
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,980
CAN YOU TELL JEANINE IN PROMOTIONS THAT I LOVED HER?

192
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,020
OF COURSE.

193
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:39,960
MR. SLAYBECK,IF YOU COULD REMEMBER ANYTHING ABOUT

194
00:09:40,090 --> 00:09:41,690
WHOEVER WAS DRIVING THE HIT-AND-RUN VEHICLE THAT KILLED YOU,

195
00:09:41,850 --> 00:09:43,060
I THINK WE CAN GET YOU SOME JUSTICE.

196
00:09:43,190 --> 00:09:45,490
WHAT HIT-AND-RUN? I WAS KILLED BY A CRASH-TEST DUMMY.

197
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:02,540
I'M NOT GOD,BUT IF I WAS, I'D BE AN ANGRY GOD.

198
00:10:02,820 --> 00:10:04,120
OH,WE GAVE IT OUR BEST SHOT.

199
00:10:04,490 --> 00:10:06,820
SO,A CRASH-TEST DUMMY KILLED BERNARD.

200
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:08,310
BERNARD WAS DELUSIONAL.

201
00:10:08,470 --> 00:10:10,320
IT'S STILL A CLUE. IT'S A DEAD END.

202
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:12,140
AND NOT THE KIND OF DEAD END YOU CAN UNDEAD

203
00:10:12,260 --> 00:10:14,780
AND THEN REDEAD AGAIN, LIKE YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO.

204
00:10:15,020 --> 00:10:15,840
IT'S MY FAULT?

205
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,790
WHEN YOU GET ALL JABBERWOCKY IN MY MINUTE,

206
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:19,640
IT'S HARD TO FOLLOW UP ON "THE DUMMY DID IT."

207
00:10:20,130 --> 00:10:21,640
GOT TO GET SOME REAL LEADS NOW.

208
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:22,950
ISN'T THAT WHAT A P.I.'s SUPPOSED TO DO?

209
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,450
INVESTIGATE? ISN'T THAT THE FUN PART?

210
00:10:24,570 --> 00:10:26,180
THE FUN PART'S COUNTING MY MONEY IN THE BUBBLE BATH.

211
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:31,490
NICE IMAGE.

212
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:36,800
OH,BOY.

213
00:10:38,190 --> 00:10:40,580
- WHAT'S THE POOP?- "THE POOP"?

214
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:43,010
THE POOP.SCOOP,SKINNY,THE HAPS,

215
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:45,610
THE DILLYO,THE 411 -- P.I. LINGO.

216
00:10:46,070 --> 00:10:47,160
RHUBARB.

217
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,110
WHAT'S THAT MEAN?

218
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:50,960
P.I. SECRET CODE FOR "GET ME A DAMN SLICE OF RHUBARB."

219
00:10:51,450 --> 00:10:53,320
THIS ISN'T PIES 'R' US, PIE CITY,

220
00:10:53,450 --> 00:10:55,030
OR THOUSANDS OF PIES IN ONE PLACE.

221
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:59,610
THIS IS A BELLS-ON-THE-DOOR, PIES-BAKING,MOM-AND-POP PLACE.

222
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:01,220
WE CHITCHAT HERE.

223
00:11:04,310 --> 00:11:05,340
CHIT!

224
00:11:07,830 --> 00:11:09,040
CHAT.

