00:23:18,430 --> 00:23:19,620
YOU WANT TO OPEN THE KIMONO

463
00:23:19,740 --> 00:23:22,210
ON WHY I'M WEARING A SILVER LEOTARD AND HANGING FROM A HOOK?

464
00:23:22,660 --> 00:23:24,390
DO YOU HAVE ANY LAST REQUESTS OR THOUGHTS?

465
00:23:25,860 --> 00:23:28,130
IF I WANTED TO MINGLE WITH A BUNCH OF GEEKS WEARING LEOTARDS,

466
00:23:28,130 --> 00:23:29,360
I'D HAVE STAYED IN ART SCHOOL.

467
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:31,180
YOU WENT TO ART SCHOOL?

468
00:23:31,300 --> 00:23:32,740
DIDN'T KNOW THAT,DID YOU?

469
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:38,660
STOP IT!

470
00:23:41,590 --> 00:23:43,530
I WAS JUST RIDING THE FERRIS WHEEL AT THE STATE FAIR,

471
00:23:43,670 --> 00:23:46,120
AND THE TEENAGER RUNNING IT SAID I COULD RIDE AN EXTRA...TURN.

472
00:23:47,350 --> 00:23:49,230
DID YOU EVER HEAR OF THE DANDY LION CAR COMPANY?

473
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:50,330
NO.

474
00:23:50,450 --> 00:23:51,210
MOVING ON. WAIT A SEC.

475
00:23:51,450 --> 00:23:53,930
I DID CHECK A BOX THAT SAID I COULD BE USED TO TEST AUTOMOBILE SAFETY.

476
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:56,670
SOUNDS SCARY,BUT WHEN YOU'RE DEAD,YOU'RE DEAD.

477
00:23:57,260 --> 00:23:58,030
AM I DEAD?

478
00:24:02,010 --> 00:24:03,760
THERE'S NOTHING ILLEGAL ABOUT ANY OF THAT?

479
00:24:03,890 --> 00:24:05,170
AND WHY WOULD DANDY LION REPLACE

480
00:24:05,290 --> 00:24:07,140
ALL THEIR CRASH-TEST DUMMIES WITH DEAD BODIES?

481
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:08,490
AND WHAT HAPPENED TO ALL THE REAL DUMMIES?

482
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:12,560
Narrator: BEFORE EMERSON COD COULD REPLY WITH A CLEVER

483
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,530
IF SLIGHTLY INSULTING REMARK...

484
00:24:14,740 --> 00:24:15,770
Shh,Shh.

485
00:24:16,700 --> 00:24:17,460
SEE THAT?

486
00:24:32,620 --> 00:24:33,610
JEANINE?

487
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:40,060
what?

488
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:46,950
I COULDN'T TELL YOU ANYTHING BEFORE BECAUSE THEY WERE WATCHING ME.

489
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:49,410
I HID AT WORK TO MAKE SURE NO ONE WOULD FOLLOW ME HOME.

490
00:24:50,330 --> 00:24:52,560
THE TRUTH IS BERNIE AND I WERE SO IN LOVE.

491
00:24:53,030 --> 00:24:55,140
IT ALL STARTED WHEN HE CAME TO SEE THIS SALES TRAINING THING

492
00:24:55,270 --> 00:24:57,050
ON HIS LONG LUNCH BREAK,AND IT WAS LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT.

493
00:24:57,050 --> 00:24:59,730
I COULDN'T TAKE MY EYES OFF HIM. HE JUST MESMERIZED ME.

494
00:24:59,860 --> 00:25:02,880
MY HEART LEAPT OUT OF MY CHEST,AND I JUST COULDN'T LOOK AWAY.

495
00:25:03,050 --> 00:25:05,690
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT WAS. I GOT ALL MISTY-EYED,YOU KNOW?

496
00:25:05,870 --> 00:25:09,000
Narrator: AND AS JEANINE CONTINUED TO EAT HER TRIPLE-BER PIE,

497
00:25:09,330 --> 00:25:12,970
SHE TOLD THEM THE STORY OF HER LOVE AFFAIR WITH BERNARD SLAYBECK.

498
00:25:14,370 --> 00:25:17,190
PRESENT,PRESENT,PRESENT,PRESENT,PRESENT,PRESENT,

499
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:20,470
AND GIGGLE,GIGGLE,GIGGLE,GIGGLE,GOOD GIRLS.

500
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:25,160
Narrator: THEY HAD MET WHEN THE SCIENTIST HAD COME TO WATCH SALES TRAINING ON A LONG LUNCH.

501
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:27,810
THE ATTRACTION WAS INSTANTANEOUS,

502
00:25:27,950 --> 00:25:31,350
AND THEY WOULD BOTH CONFESS TO REPLAYING THIS FIRST ENCOUNTER

503
00:25:31,470 --> 00:25:34,190
AS THEY FELL ASLEEP IN THEIR BEDS THAT NIGHT.

504
00:25:36,750 --> 00:25:39,580
HE WOULD REMEMBER HER HAIR AS BEING SLIGHTLY REDDER,

505
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:41,610
HER SWEATER SLIGHTLY TIGHTER,

506
00:25:41,900 --> 00:25:44,710
BUT THE SMILE HE WOULD GET JUST RIGHT.

507
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:50,090
SHE WOULD REMEMBER HIS LOOK AS SHY BUT FLIRTATIOUS,

508
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:52,500
HIS TIE AS RED BUT VERY THIN,

509
00:25:52,710 --> 00:25:54,710
AND THAT HIS SANDWICH WAS AN ANGUS BEEF PATTY

510
00:25:54,820 --> 00:25:56,930
WITH BUTTERHEAD LETTUCE,ROMA TOMATOES,

511
00:25:57,070 --> 00:25:59,030
ON A SESAME-SEED WHOLE-WHEAT BUN,

512
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:01,170
AND A GLASS OF 2% MILK.

513
00:26:03,290 --> 00:26:06,740
AS THEY TALKED,THESE ARE THE THINGS SHE CAME TO KNOW FIRST.

514
00:26:06,880 --> 00:26:10,100
THE SCIENTIST WAS KIND. THE SCIENTIST WAS LONELY.

515
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:13,100
THE SCIENTIST CAME ALIVE WHEN HE TOLD HER

516
00:26:13,250 --> 00:26:15,450
ABOUT HIS HOBBY OF CATCHING BUTTERFLIES.

517
00:26:15,660 --> 00:26:18,690
WHEN HE ADMITTED THAT HE ALWAYS SET THEM FREE,

518
00:26:19,050 --> 00:26:22,320
SHE FELT DIZZY AND GIGGLED FOR NO REASON.

519
00:26:32,830 --> 00:26:36,120
Narrator: THE WAIF AND THE SCIENTIST FELL DEEPLY IN LOVE,

520
00:26:36,260 --> 00:26:39,490
HIDING THEIR AFFAIR FROM THE WORLD LIKE A TRADE SECRET.

521
00:26:48,370 --> 00:26:52,410
BUT JEANINE FROM PROMOTIONS FELT A CHASM GROWING BETWEEN THEM.

522
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:58,390
AS THE LAUNCH OF THE FLOWER CAR GREW CLOSER,

523
00:26:58,520 --> 00:27:00,180
BERNARD'S HOURS GREW LONGER.

524
00:27:08,310 --> 00:27:10,490
HE BECAME DISTANT AND HARD TO REACH.

525
00:27:14,620 --> 00:27:17,850
SUSPECTING HER SAFETY SCIENTIST OF STEPPING OUT ON HER,

526
00:27:18,100 --> 00:27:19,790
SHE BEGAN TO SPY.

527
00:27:19,930 --> 00:27:21,440
BUT THERE WAS NO OTHER FLOWER,

528
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:24,410
ONLY MYSTERIOUS TRIPS INTO THE DARKNESS.

529
00:27:33,090 --> 00:27:34,110
WHERE DID SHE GO?

530
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:36,930
SORRY. RESTROOM. MINT,ANYONE?

531
00:27:37,570 --> 00:27:38,520
NO,THANKS.

532
00:27:38,660 --> 00:27:40,410
WHERE WAS SLAYBECK GOING ON THESE NIGHT DRIVES?

533
00:27:40,530 --> 00:27:41,430
I COULD NEVER SEE.

534
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:42,630
AND WHEN I CONFRONTED HIM ABOUT IT,

535
00:27:42,770 --> 00:27:43,630
HE WOULDN'T TELL ME ANYTHING.

536
00:27:43,990 --> 00:27:46,100
I THOUGHT I WAS BEING PARANOID TILL HTURNED UP DEAD.

537
00:27:47,290 --> 00:27:48,840
YOU GONNA FINISH THAT? YES.

538
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:50,580
I WISH WE KNEW WHAT HE WAS DOING.

539
00:27:51,050 --> 00:27:52,100
OH,I FIGURED IT OUT. [ CHUCKLES ]

540
00:28:25,070 --> 00:28:26,990
IT'S EASIER IF I SHOW YOU. FOLLOW ME.

541
00:28:27,100 --> 00:28:28,330
SHOTGUN! CHUCK!

542
00:28:28,330 --> 00:28:29,460
I HATE THE BACK.

543
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:31,590
DEAD,AGAIN,FOREVER.

544
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:33,440
FINE.

545
00:28:42,990 --> 00:28:44,120
Chuck: SHE'S NOT GOING VERY FAST.

546
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:45,830
Ned: THAT CAR CAN'T HAVE A VERY BIG ENGINE.

547
00:28:46,030 --> 00:28:47,020
MAYBE SHE ATE IT.

548
00:28:47,830 --> 00:28:49,110
THAT'S NOT FUNNY.

549
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:50,810
SHE OBVIOUSLY HAS A VERY SERIOUS DISORDER.

550
00:28:51,030 --> 00:28:52,760
WHAT DO YOU MEAN? SERIOUSLY?

551
00:28:52,890 --> 00:28:54,880
THE GIRL'S GOT A WHOLE SECRET LIFE IN THE BATHROOM.

552
00:28:55,230 --> 00:28:56,800
AND I KNOW EXACTLY HOW SHE FEELS.

553
00:28:56,970 --> 00:28:57,910
SO DO I.

554
00:28:58,050 --> 00:28:59,860
I HATE HAVING SECRETS. NOW I AM ONE --

555
00:28:59,990 --> 00:29:02,380
ALL THESE DISGUISES,HIDING IN YOUR APARTMENT ALL THE TIME.

556
00:29:02,530 --> 00:29:04,670
I HATE SECRETS,TOO. YOU LOVE SECRETS.

557
00:29:04,790 --> 00:29:07,620
YOU WANT TO MARRY SECRETS AND HAVE LITTLE HALF-SECRET,HALF-HUMAN BABIES.

558
00:29:09,310 --> 00:29:10,900
WELL,I HAVE A SECRET,TOO. I DO MISS MY AUNTS.

559
00:29:10,900 --> 00:29:13,380
THEN ALL I HAVE IS YOU.

560
00:29:13,570 --> 00:29:14,970
WHICH IS GREAT,BUT...

561
00:29:15,560 --> 00:29:17,410
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT YOU SINCYOU WERE 9.

562
00:29:17,660 --> 00:29:19,270
IT'S PRETTY MUCH I BAKE PIES AND WAKE THE DEAD.

563
00:29:19,410 --> 00:29:20,660
I LIVE A VERY SHELTERED LIFE.

564
00:29:20,790 --> 00:29:22,350
I ALREADY LIVED A SHELTERED LIFE ONCE.

565
00:29:23,860 --> 00:29:25,500
BUT IT WASN'T AS SHELTERED AS YOU THINK.

566
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:29,630
AUNT LILY HAD A VERY EXTENSIVE COLLECTION OF HISTORIC EROTICA HIDDEN IN THE MILK CELLAR.

567
00:29:29,780 --> 00:29:31,060
THE MILK CELLAR.

568
00:29:31,180 --> 00:29:33,450
THE CHEESE FLOOR,THE SPOOKY PLACE UNDER THE HOUSE,WHATEVER.

569
00:29:33,650 --> 00:29:36,060
I WILL PAY BOTH OF YOU NOT TO HAVE THIS CONVERSATION IN FRONT OF ME.

570
00:29:36,060 --> 00:29:39,130
IT'S NOT IN FRONT OF YOU. IT'S TO THE SIDE AND BEHIND YOU.

571
00:29:39,260 --> 00:29:40,590
YOU CAN'T RIDE IN THE FRONT,CHUCK.

572
00:29:41,050 --> 00:29:42,750
Narrator: TRAGICALLY FOR JEANINE,

573
00:29:42,890 --> 00:29:44,950
IT DIDN'T MATTER WHERE SHE SAT.

574
00:30:03,980 --> 00:30:05,570
THERE YOU GO. GOOD AS NEW.

575
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:06,820
DO I LOOK OKAY?

576
00:30:06,960 --> 00:30:08,600
RUNWAY READY. REALLY?

577
00:30:08,810 --> 00:30:10,670
YOU DON'T THINK THESE BANDAGES MAKE ME LOOK FAT?

578
00:30:10,930 --> 00:30:12,030
NO,NOT AT ALL.

579
00:30:12,170 --> 00:30:15,610
THAT'S SO SWEET. IS HE ALWAYS THIS SWEET?

580
00:30:15,610 --> 00:30:16,510
I WOULDN'T KNOW.

581
00:30:16,630 --> 00:30:18,950
LOOK,SOME CAR BOMBER JUST WENT THROUGH A LOT OF TROUBLE

582
00:30:19,070 --> 00:30:21,250
TO KEEP YOU FROM SHOWING US WHATEVER IT IS YOU WANTED TO SHOW US.

583
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:22,720
THE BODIES.

584
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:24,260
WHAT BODIES? THE DEAD BODIES?

585
00:30:24,380 --> 00:30:25,530
WE ALREADY FOUND THE DEAD BODIES.

586
00:30:25,530 --> 00:30:28,880
NO. THE ONES IN THE BIG HOLE.

587
00:30:39,230 --> 00:30:40,160
HOW SAD.

588
00:30:40,300 --> 00:30:41,510
WHY WOULD SOMEBODY DO THIS?

589
00:30:43,100 --> 00:30:44,210
ONE WAY TO FIND OUT.

590
00:30:49,190 --> 00:30:50,190
WHAT IS ALL THAT?

591
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:53,100
EACH ONE OF THESE GUYS IS FITTED WITH A COMPUTER HARD DRIVE

592
00:30:53,230 --> 00:30:54,990
TO RECORD ANY OF THE CRASH-TEST DATA.

593
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:57,140
YOU BURY THE DUMMIES,YOU BURY THE DATA.

594
00:30:57,280 --> 00:30:58,610
COULDN'T THEY JUST ERASE IT?

595
00:30:58,820 --> 00:31:00,650
YOU NEVER CAN COMPLETELY ERASE ANYTHING.

596
00:31:00,790 --> 00:31:04,090
WHY ARE DEAD PEOPLE ON HOOKS AND PLASTIC DUMMIES IN A GRAVE?

597
00:31:04,260 --> 00:31:05,940
THE COMPANY MUST HAVE SWITCHED TO CADAVERS

598
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:08,410
SO THAT THERE'D BE NO PERMANENT RECORD OF THE CRASH-TEST RESULTS,

599
00:31:08,410 --> 00:31:09,810
'CAUSE DEAD PEOPLE DON'T TALK...

600
00:31:09,940 --> 00:31:11,740
USUALLY.

601
00:31:29,670 --> 00:31:31,380
Narrator: AS THE PIE MAKER'S BRAIN CRACKLED

602
00:31:31,380 --> 00:31:35,730
WITH 10,000 VOLTS OF ELECTRICITY AND THEN LOST CONSCIOUSNESS,

603
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:37,800
OLIVE WOULD HAVE NO SUCH LUCK.

604
00:31:37,940 --> 00:31:39,350
DIGBY,YOU AWAKE?

605
00:31:41,600 --> 00:31:43,090
I CAN'T SLEEP,EITHER.

606
00:31:43,260 --> 00:31:44,960
Narrator: CLOSING HER EYES ONLY MADE HER VISIONS

607
00:31:45,100 --> 00:31:47,070
OF THE PIE MAKER'S LATE-NIGHT DATE

608
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:49,000
WITH THE PERKY BRUNETTE FROM NOWHERE

609
00:31:49,140 --> 00:31:51,100
MORE VIVID AND UNCENSORED.

610
00:31:58,120 --> 00:31:59,970
OH! YUCK.

611
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:03,220
Narrator: OLIVE DECIDED SHE WAS DONE LYING DOWN ABOUT THIS.

612
00:32:05,190 --> 00:32:07,360
WE ARE UP. WE ARE WALKING.

613
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:26,430
[ Muffled ] LOOK.

614
00:32:45,330 --> 00:32:48,000
AUTOMOBILE MANUFACTURING IS A DIRTY BUSINESS.

615
00:32:48,130 --> 00:32:50,780
Narrator: MURDER WAS NOT NEW FOR MARK CHASE.

616
00:32:50,940 --> 00:32:53,840
LUCKILY,BODY BAGS KEEP THINGS NICE AND NEAT.

617
00:32:55,740 --> 00:32:57,270
Narrator: THE FACTS WERE THESE.

618
00:32:57,430 --> 00:32:59,710
THROUGH A SERIES OF CRASH-TEST EXPEMENTS,

619
00:32:59,870 --> 00:33:02,180
BERNARD SLAYBE HAD LEARNED THAT THE DANDY LION

620
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:03,890
WAS A DEADLY DUD.

621
00:33:14,290 --> 00:33:17,240
BERNARD BEGGED THE PRESIDENT TO CANCEL THE CAR'S LAUNCH,

622
00:33:17,550 --> 00:33:20,270
BUT MARK CHASE HAD OTHER PLANS.

623
00:33:25,230 --> 00:33:29,080
LIKE A SMOKING GUN,THE SMOKING DUMMIES WOULD HAVE TO BE BURIED.

624
00:33:29,490 --> 00:33:32,500
THE COMPANY HAD INVESTED MILLIONS IN THE DANDY LION,

625
00:33:32,650 --> 00:33:34,790
AND HE KNEW THAT KEEPING THIS TERRIBLE SECRET

626
00:33:34,940 --> 00:33:38,370
WOULD STILL BE CHEAPER THAN HALTING PRODUCTION OF THE CAR.

627
00:33:43,070 --> 00:33:45,490
A DECISION WAS MADE,A COVER-UP UNDERTAKEN.

628
00:33:45,630 --> 00:33:47,530
IF THE DUMMIES HAD TO GO,

629
00:33:47,690 --> 00:33:50,560
SO WOULD ANY DUMMY WHO GOT IN THE WAY.

630
00:34:08,820 --> 00:34:12,220
AS HE REGAINED CONSCIOUSNESS AND HURTLED TOWARD THE CRASH-TEST WALL,

631
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:14,880
BERNARD'S ONLY THOUGHTS WERE OF JEANINE

632
00:34:15,010 --> 00:34:17,520
AND HOW HE WISHED HE'D TOLD HER HE LOVED HER.

633
00:34:26,210 --> 00:34:29,370
MARK CHASE'S ATTENTION TO DETAIL AND GIFT FOR PLANNING

634
00:34:29,530 --> 00:34:34,060
HAD SERVED HIM WELL AS A C.E.O.,AND NOW AGAIN AS A MURDERER.

635
00:34:34,230 --> 00:34:35,400
HIS COVER-UP COMPLETE,

636
00:34:35,540 --> 00:34:38,000
HIS ONLY THOUGHTS WERE THAT THE DANDY LION SX

637
00:34:38,130 --> 00:34:41,470
WOULD BLOOM ON TIME AND NO ONE WOULD STOP HIM.

638
00:34:46,190 --> 00:34:48,820
THE DANDY LION CAR IS THE CULMINATION OF MY LIFE'S WORK.

639
00:34:48,950 --> 00:34:50,250
IT IS A FLOWER-POWERED PHENOMENON

640
00:34:50,380 --> 00:34:51,660
BORNE OF A THOUSAND SLEEPLESS NIGHTS,

641
00:34:51,790 --> 00:34:52,850
INTENSE RITALIN ABUSE,

642
00:34:52,980 --> 00:34:54,870
AND A LONG-SUBLIMATED INTEREST IN BOTANY.

643
00:34:55,030 --> 00:34:58,510
SO WHAT IF IN THE UNLIKELY BUT NOT IMPOSSIBLE EVENT

644
00:34:58,650 --> 00:35:00,470
THAT THE CAR GETS UP TO A SPEED OF 70 MILES AN HOUR,

645
00:35:00,590 --> 00:35:02,230
WITH THE HEADLIGHTS ON AND THE SEAT WARMER ON LOW,

646
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,620
A SHORT-CIRCUIT IN THE RADIO

647
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:05,420
CAUSES A CATACLYSMIC CHAIN REACTION

648
00:35:05,540 --> 00:35:08,340
THAT BLOWS THE CAR AND ITS PRECIOUS HUMAN CARGO TO SMITHEREENS?!

649
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:11,210
Narrator: AS MARK CHASE CONTINUED HIS MONOLOGUE,

650
00:35:11,350 --> 00:35:13,530
UNAWARE THAT IT WAS COMPLETELY INAUDIBLE

651
00:35:13,670 --> 00:35:16,490
FROM WITHIN THE SEALED BODY BAGS WITHIN THE CAR,

652
00:35:16,970 --> 00:35:20,490
CHUCK PONDERED WHY IT WAS SHE ALWAYS SEEMED TO DIE

653
00:35:20,670 --> 00:35:23,170
JUST AS THINGS WERE STARTING TO GET GOOD.

654
00:35:24,770 --> 00:35:25,790
SON OF A BITCH.

655
00:35:25,950 --> 00:35:27,100
WHAT?

656
00:35:27,220 --> 00:35:28,710
Narrator: AND THOUGH HE COULDN'T HEAR HER,

657
00:35:28,860 --> 00:35:31,350
NED SUDDENLY WANTED TO TELL HER EVERYTHING --

658
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:33,720
PET PEEVES AND FAVORITE FOODS,

659
00:35:33,890 --> 00:35:35,800
HIS FEARS,HIS DREAMS,

660
00:35:35,940 --> 00:35:39,010
AND ALL THE PURE JOY SHE HAD BROUGHT INTO HIS LIFE.

661
00:35:41,390 --> 00:35:42,680
SAYONARA.

662
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:46,270
Narrator: THIS WAS THE END ALL OVER AGAIN.

663
00:35:47,640 --> 00:35:48,760
GOODBYE.

664
00:36:13,490 --> 00:36:15,750
Narrator: EMERSON COD DID NOT LIKE TO KNIT IN PUBLIC,

665
00:36:16,160 --> 00:36:18,740
BUT HE OFTEN LEFT THE HOUSE WITH THE NEEDLES IN HIS POCKET,

666
00:36:18,870 --> 00:36:22,980
SHOULD THE OPPORTUNITY TO RIB-STITCH A SKI CAP PRESENT ITSELF.

667
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:31,790
DRIVE! OOH!

668
00:36:54,430 --> 00:36:57,060
Narrator: IF ONLY THE PIE MAKER HAD HEARD THE KILLER EXPLAIN

669
00:36:57,250 --> 00:37:01,340
THAT THE DANDY LION SX WAS MUCH MORE THAN AN ECO-FRIENDLY CAR OF THE FUTURE.

670
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:04,550
IF ONLY HE'D HEARD IT WAS ALSO A DEATHTRAP,

671
00:37:04,670 --> 00:37:07,280
A DANDELION-FUELED TIME BOMB.

672
00:37:13,890 --> 00:37:15,970
COME ON. JUST A LITTLE FASTER.

673
00:37:25,770 --> 00:37:27,700
CAN'T THIS CAR GO ANY FASTER?!

674
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:29,210
SOME CAR OF THE FUTURE THIS IS!

675
00:37:29,330 --> 00:37:30,830
I THOUGHT THE CAR OF THE FUTURE WAS SUPPOSED TO FLY.

676
00:37:30,970 --> 00:37:32,200
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED TO FLYING CARS?

677
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:03,310
Narrator: IN THE UNLIKELY BUT NOT IMPOSSIBLE EVENT

678
00:38:03,450 --> 00:38:05,780
OF REACHING THE SPEED OF 70 MILES AN HOUR

679
00:38:05,930 --> 00:38:08,800
WITH THE HEADLIGHTS ON AND THE SEAT WARMER SET TO LOW,

680
00:38:08,950 --> 00:38:10,550
A SHORT-CIRCUIT IN THE RADIO

681
00:38:10,700 --> 00:38:13,280
WOULD SET OFF A CATACLYSMIC CHAIN REACTION

682
00:38:13,430 --> 00:38:17,800
THAT WOULD BLOW THE CAR AND ITS PRECIOUS HUMAN CARGO TO SMITHEREENS.

683
